The paper deals with the complexity of search problems and interactive proofs, which are topics typically studied in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The specific problems studied in the paper, such as linear programming and 3-SUM, are also commonly studied in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization and graph theory, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT).
